A function is a reusable block of code
            that you can run whenever you want


            Basic Syntax
function greet() {
  console.log("Hello");
}
🔍 Break it down
function → keyword (you’re creating a function)
greet → the name of the function
() → where inputs (parameters) go
{} → the code that runs


const stella = function() {
  console.log("Hi, I'm Stella!");
};

2. Function expression
const sayHi = function() {
  console.log("Hi");
};







3. Arrow function (modern)
const sayHi = () => {
  console.log("Hi");
};





function toggle(1,3){
    1+3
}
toggle(2,7)








